%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22MEA%20Reiterates%20it%20Is%20Pursuing%20Discharge%20of%20Indians%20Lured%20Into%20Russian%20Army%20as%20More%20Reports%20Emerge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04230638%2FEffect-12.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20With%20more%20cases%20of%20Indians%20being%20reportedly%20conned%20into%20joining%20the%20fight%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20behalf%20in%20Ukraine%20coming%20to%20the%20fore%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20reiterated%20that%20it%20has%20taken%20up%20%E2%80%9Ceach%20and%20every%E2%80%9D%20case%20with%20Russian%20authorities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20there%20were%20reports%20suggesting%20that%20over%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fover-100-indians-recruited-as-army-helpers-in-russia-report%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E100%20Indian%20nationals%20may%20have%20been%20recruited%20as%20security%20helpers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20Russian%20Army.%20Many%20alleged%20that%20they%20were%20coerced%20into%20combat%20areas%20alongside%20Russian%20forces%2C%20despite%20assurances%20that%20they%20would%20not%20be%20deployed%20in%20active%20conflict%20zones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Saturday%2C%20it%20was%20reported%20that%20a%2023-year-old%20man%20from%20Gujarat%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2F23-year-old-indian-national-hired-as-security-helper-in-russia-killed-in-war-zone%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewas%20killed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20a%20Ukrainian%20air%20strike%20in%20the%20Donetsk%20region%20on%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20border%20on%20February%2021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fjob-fraud-kashmiri-conned-into-fighting-for-russian-army-against-ukraine%2Fcid%2F2002938%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20new%20media%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Students%20Association%20claimed%20that%20two%20men%20from%20Kashmir%20were%20fraudulently%20lured%20to%20fight%20for%20the%20Russian%20army%20in%20Ukraine.%20While%20one%20of%20them%20has%20been%20injured%2C%20another%20is%20reportedly%20missing.%20They%20claimed%20to%20have%20written%20to%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%2C%20urging%20for%20the%20repatriation%20of%20the%20two%20men.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37661%2FMedia%2Breports%2Bregarding%2BIndian%2Bnationals%2Bseeking%2Bdischarge%2Bfrom%2Bthe%2BRussian%2BArmy%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20MEA%20on%20Monday%20claimed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20these%20were%20%E2%80%9Cinaccurate%E2%80%9D%20reports%20in%20the%20media.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CEach%20and%20every%20such%20case%20brought%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Indian%20Embassy%20in%20Moscow%20has%20been%20strongly%20taken%20up%20with%20the%20Russian%20authorities%20and%20those%20brought%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Ministry%20have%20been%20taken%20up%20with%20the%20Russian%20Embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Several%20Indians%20have%20already%20been%20discharged%20as%20a%20result%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20MEA%20press%20note.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20MEA%20added%20that%20it%20was%20actively%20pursuing%20all%20cases%20of%20Indian%20nationals%20for%20an%20early%20discharge%20from%20the%20Russian%20army%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmatter%20of%20top%20priority%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20modus%20operandi%20of%20the%20Kashmiri%20men%20reaching%20Russia%20was%20largely%20similarly%20to%20previous%20cases%20%E2%80%93%20they%20had%20been%20lured%20through%20promises%20made%20in%20a%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20%E2%80%98Baba%20Vlogs%E2%80%99%20operated%20by%20Dubai-based%20consultant%20called%20Faisal%20Khan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20information%20provided%20by%20one%20of%20the%20Kashmiri%20men%2C%20Azad%20Yusuf%20Kumar%20from%20Pulwama%E2%80%99s%20Awantipora%2C%20the%20JKSA%20said%20that%20on%20arrival%20in%20Russia%2C%20they%20were%20made%20to%20sign%20agreements%20in%20Russian%20which%20they%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20comprehend.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubsequently%2C%20they%20were%20transferred%20to%20the%20Russian%20army%2C%20where%20they%20underwent%20a%2015-day%20training%20program%20before%20being%20dispatched%20to%20the%20Ukraine%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAzad%20has%20reportedly%20sustained%20injuries%20and%20is%20currently%20stranded%20at%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20border.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20family%20has%20provided%20documentation%20of%20the%20signed%20agreement%20in%20Russian%2C%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20current%20location%2C%20his%20photograph%2C%20and%20his%20IMO%20(International%20Maritime%20Organisation)%20number%2C%20which%20he%20has%20been%20using%20to%20contact%20them%20intermittently%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20JKSA%20spokesman%20stated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20individual%20from%20Kashmir%2C%20identified%20as%20Zahoor%20Ahmad%20Sheikh%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Kupwara%E2%80%99s%20Tangdhar%20area%2C%20is%20missing.%20Zahoor%20had%20travelled%20to%20Russia%20last%20December%2C%20reportedly%20accompanied%20by%20two%20other%20men%20from%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fresponse-to-queries.htm%3Fdtl%2F37653%2FOfficial%2BSpokespersons%2Bresponse%2Bto%2Bmedia%2Bqueries%2Bregarding%2BIndians%2Bcaught%2Bin%2Bconflict%2Bin%2BRussia%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20Friday%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%20had%20urged%20%E2%80%9Call%20Indian%20nationals%20to%20exercise%20due%20caution%20and%20stay%20away%20from%20this%20conflict%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708939786000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmea-reiterates-it-is-pursuing-discharge-of-indians-lured-into-russian-army-as-more-reports-emerge%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CEach%20and%20every%20such%20case%20brought%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Indian%20Embassy%20in%20Moscow%20has%20been%20strongly%20taken%20up%20with%20the%20Russian%20authorities...%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmea-reiterates-it-is-pursuing-discharge-of-indians-lured-into-russian-army-as-more-reports-emerge%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Air%20Force%20man%20sets%20himself%20on%20fire%20at%20US%20Israeli%20embassy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708939557000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F60B1%2Fproduction%2F_132735742_gettyimages-2031352382.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68398479%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20member%20of%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20is%20in%20a%20critical%20condition%20after%20the%20incident%20in%20Washington%20on%20Sunday%20afternoon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A193%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68398479%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68398479.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68398479.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Humiliation%20and%20the%20Upending%20of%20Poll%20Narratives%3A%20The%20Impact%20of%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Judgment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F09172044%2FScreen-Shot-2021-03-09-at-5.20.25-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cartoonistsatish.com%2Freveal-the-names-of-donors%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecartoon%20by%20Satish%20Acharya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20must%20have%20hurt%2C%20especially%20as%20it%20is%20covered%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20our%20constitution%2C%20which%20was%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20calling%20card%20for%20dumping%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scheme%20was%20touted%20as%20the%20panacea%20for%20eradicating%20black%20money%20from%20elections%2C%20but%20was%20ironically%20seen%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20itself%20as%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20with%20corporates%20%E2%80%93%20a%20form%20of%20institutionalised%20corruption.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20humiliation%20comes%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20the%20complete%20failure%20to%20honour%20the%20promise%2C%20first%20made%20in%20detail%20on%20the%20February%2012%2C%202014%20episode%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EChai%20Pe%20Charcha%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20of%20bringing%20back%20black-money%20not%20only%20from%20Swiss%20banks%20and%20tax%20free%20havens%2C%20but%20also%2C%20later%2C%20from%20domestic%20hoarders%20through%20the%20painful%20experiment%20of%20demonetisation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%20are%20seven%20key%20takeaways%20from%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgement%20and%20its%20immediate%20aftermath%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20silence%20on%20the%20right%20to%20information%20being%20an%20end%20in%20itself%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPerhaps%20the%20most%20powerful%20observation%20of%20the%20court%20was%20made%20in%20paragraph%2065%20of%20its%20judgement%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20right%20to%20information%20has%20an%20intrinsic%20constitutional%20value%3B%20one%20that%20recognises%20that%20it%20is%20not%20just%20a%20means%20to%20an%20end%20but%20an%20end%20in%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20deafening%20silence%20on%20the%20verdict%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20celebrations%20following%20the%20judgements%20on%20Rafale%2C%20Article%20370%20and%20the%20Ayodhya%20Ram%20Mandir%2C%20had%20ominous%20echoes%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fin-effective-reversal-of-sc-order-union-govt-takes-back-control-of-services-in-delhi%5C%22%3Eswift%20undoing%20of%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20bench%20judgement%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20May%2011%2C%202023%2C%20which%20had%20given%20control%20over%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20civil%20%E2%80%98services%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20government%2C%20by%20promulgating%20an%20ordinance%20on%20May%2019%2C%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20as%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20judgement%20goes%20to%20the%20core%20constitutional%20values%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20and%20democracy%2C%20it%20would%20be%20hazardous%20for%20the%20government%20to%20annul%2C%20through%20an%20ordinance%2C%20the%20operative%20part%20of%20the%20judgement%2C%20which%20is%20as%20follows%20(paragraph%20219)%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20SBI%20%5BState%20Bank%20of%20India%5D%20shall%20submit%20details%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20purchased%20since%20the%20interim%20order%20of%20this%20Court%20dated%2012%20April%202019%20till%20date%20to%20the%20ECI%20%5BElection%20Commission%20of%20India%5D.%20The%20details%20shall%20include%20the%20date%20of%20purchase%20of%20each%20Electoral%20Bond%2C%20the%20name%20of%20the%20purchaser%20of%20the%20bond%20and%20the%20denomination%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20purchased%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSBI%20shall%20submit%20the%20details%20of%20political%20parties%20which%20have%20received%20contributions%20through%20Electoral%20Bonds%20since%20the%20interim%20order%20of%20this%20Court%20dated%2012%20April%202019%20till%20date%20to%20the%20ECI.%20SBI%20must%20disclose%20details%20of%20each%20Electoral%20Bond%20encashed%20by%20political%20parties%20which%20shall%20include%20the%20date%20of%20encashment%20and%20the%20denomination%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSBI%20shall%20submit%20the%20above%20information%20to%20the%20ECI%20within%20three%20weeks%20from%20the%20date%20of%20this%20judgment%2C%20that%20is%2C%20by%206%20March%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ECI%20shall%20publish%20the%20information%20shared%20by%20the%20SBI%20on%20its%20official%20website%20within%20one%20week%20of%20the%20receipt%20of%20the%20information%2C%20that%20is%2C%20by%2013%20March%202024.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%5C%22%3EElection%20Commission%20Has%20No%20Comments%20on%20Landmark%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Verdict%3A%20How%20it%20Changed%20its%20Stance%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENexus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cb%3Ebetween%20basic%20structure%2C%20democracy%20and%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20has%20held%20that%20public%20knowledge%20of%20the%20contributions%20made%20by%20companies%20to%20political%20parties%20is%20necessary%20for%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20to%20safeguard%20democracy%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98basic%20structure%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDrawing%20a%20nexus%20between%20the%20basic%20structure%2C%20democracy%20and%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%2C%20it%20observed%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20democratic%20set%20up%20of%20government%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20features%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Elections%20matter%20in%20democracy%20because%20they%20are%20the%20most%20profound%20expression%20of%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20%E2%80%A6%20The%20integrity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%20is%20a%20necessary%20concomitant%20to%20the%20maintenance%20of%20the%20democratic%20form%20of%20government.%E2%80%9D%20(paragraph%20202).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%2C%20in%20paragraph%20203%2C%20it%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20Court%20has%20also%20consistently%20held%20that%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20form%20an%20important%20concomitant%20of%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECalling%20out%20institutionalised%20corruption%20and%20quid%20pro%20quo%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20the%20court%2C%20the%20unveiling%20of%20opaque%20electoral%20bonds%20was%20necessary%20not%20only%20to%20ensure%20that%20voters%20had%20the%20right%20to%20information%20guaranteed%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20our%20constitution%2C%20but%20also%20for%20unmasking%20institutionalised%20corruption.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20remarked%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20deletion%20of%20the%20mandate%20of%20disclosing%20the%20particulars%20of%20contributions%20violates%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20voter%20since%20they%20would%20not%20possess%20information%20about%20the%20political%20party%20to%20which%20the%20contribution%20was%20made%20which%2C%20as%20we%20have%20held%20above%2C%20is%20necessary%20to%20identify%20corruption%20and%20quid%20pro%20quo%20transactions%20in%20governance.%E2%80%9D%20(Paragraph%20172)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20repeatedly%20referred%20to%20quid%20pro%20quo%20between%20donors%20and%20the%20receiving%20political%20party%20which%20is%20in%20power.%20In%20paragraph%20167%2C%20it%20referred%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinfluence%20of%20money%20in%20electoral%20politics%20(through%20electoral%20outcomes)%20and%20governmental%20decisions%20(through%20a%20seat%20at%20the%20table%20and%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%20between%20the%20contributor%20and%20the%20political%20party)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20paragraph%20201%2C%20the%20court%20bluntly%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20reason%20for%20political%20contributions%20by%20companies%20is%20as%20open%20as%20day%20light%20%5Bsic%5D.%20Even%20the%20learned%20Solicitor%20General%20did%20not%20deny%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearings%20that%20corporate%20donations%20are%20made%20to%20receive%20favours%20through%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20made%20it%20crystal%20clear%20in%20paragraph%20212%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccontributions%20made%20by%20companies%20are%20purely%20business%20transactions%20made%20with%20the%20intent%20of%20securing%20benefits%20in%20return.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fquid-pro-quo-how-revealing-electoral-bonds-will-clear-questions-of-len-den%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Quid-Pro-Quo%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20Revealing%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Will%20Clear%20Questions%20of%20%E2%80%98Len-Den%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERubbishing%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claim%20of%20it%20not%20knowing%20the%20identity%20of%20donors%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20holding%2C%20in%20paragraph%20104%2C%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20violative%20of%20Article%2019(1)(a)%2C%20the%20court%20systematically%20(in%20paragraph%20103)%20rubbished%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20it%20did%20not%20know%20who%20the%20donors%20were.%20The%20court%20observed%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20submission%20of%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20is%20that%20the%20political%20party%20which%20receives%20the%20contribution%20does%20not%20know%20of%20identity%20of%20the%20contributor%20because%20neither%20the%20bond%20would%20have%20their%20name%20nor%20could%20the%20bank%20discloses%20%5Bsic%5D%20such%20details%20to%20the%20political%20party.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20agree%20with%20this%20submission.%20While%20it%20is%20true%20that%20the%20law%20prescribes%20anonymity%20as%20a%20central%20characteristic%20of%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20de%20jure%20anonymity%20of%20the%20contributors%20does%20not%20translate%20to%20de%20facto%20anonymity.%20The%20Scheme%20is%20not%20fool-proof.%20There%20are%20sufficient%20gaps%20in%20the%20Scheme%20which%20enable%20political%20parties%20to%20know%20the%20particulars%20of%20the%20contributions%20made%20to%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CClause%2012%20of%20the%20Scheme%20states%20that%20the%20bond%20can%20be%20encashed%20only%20by%20the%20political%20party%20by%20depositing%20it%20in%20the%20designated%20bank%20account.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20contributor%20could%20physically%20hand%20over%20the%20electoral%20bond%20to%20an%20office%20bearer%20of%20the%20political%20party%20or%20to%20the%20legislator%20belonging%20to%20the%20political%20party%2C%20or%20it%20could%20have%20been%20sent%20to%20the%20office%20of%20the%20political%20party%20with%20the%20name%20of%20the%20contributor%2C%20or%20the%20contributor%20could%20after%20depositing%20the%20electoral%20bond%20disclose%20the%20particulars%20of%20the%20contribution%20to%20a%20member%20of%20the%20political%20party%20for%20them%20to%20cross-verify.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20according%20to%20the%20data%20on%20contributions%20made%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20ninety%20four%20percent%20of%20the%20contributions%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20have%20been%20made%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20one%20crore.%20Electoral%20bonds%20provide%20economically%20resourced%20contributors%20who%20already%20have%20a%20seat%20at%20the%20table%20selective%20anonymity%20vis-a%CC%80-vis%20the%20public%20and%20not%20the%20political%20party.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01232023%2FEffect-8-1024x478.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01232023%2FEffect-8-1024x478.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01232023%2FEffect-8-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01232023%2FEffect-8.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687344%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22392%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EUnless%20donor%20identities%20are%20blocked%20through%20an%20ordinance%2C%20this%20may%20be%20the%20first%20time%20the%20electoral%20narrative%20may%20be%20controlled%20not%20by%20Narendra%20Modi%20but%20by%20the%20fallout%20from%20the%20apex%20court%20direction%20on%20electoral%20bonds.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40narendramodi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EElectoral%20bonds%20and%20shell%20companies%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20Independence%20Day%20speech%20in%202017%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20claimed%20that%20his%20government%20had%20unearthed%20over%203%2C00%2C000%20shell%20companies%20and%20that%20he%20had%20%E2%80%9Cwaged%20a%20big%20war%20against%20corruption%20and%20black%20money%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%20on%20September%2020%2C%202020%20that%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Corporate%20Affairs%20had%20removed%20the%20names%20of%203%2C82%2C581%20companies%20from%20the%20official%20records%20following%20what%20the%20government%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9Cspecial%20drive%20for%20identification%20and%20strike%20off%20shell%20companies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20July%2027%2C%202021%2C%20a%20junior%20Union%20corporate%20affairs%20minister%20informed%20parliament%20that%20the%20government%20had%20identified%202%2C38%2C223%20companies%20as%20shell%20companies.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%20one%20of%20the%20most%20damaging%20observations%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20about%20the%20possible%20mushrooming%20of%20shell%20companies%20because%20of%20the%20removal%20of%20limits%20to%20donations%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20paragraph%20208%2C%20the%20court%20observed%20as%20follows%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20ostensible%20object%20of%20the%20amendment%2C%20as%20contended%20by%20the%20learned%20Solicitor%20General%2C%20was%20to%20discourage%20the%20creation%20of%20shell%20companies%2C%20there%20is%20no%20justification%20for%20removing%20the%20cap%20on%20contributions%20which%20was%20included%20for%20the%20very%20same%20purpose%3A%20to%20deter%20shell%20companies%20from%20making%20political%20contributions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20when%20the%20proposal%20to%20amend%20Section%20182%20of%20the%202013%20%5BCompanies%5D%20Act%20was%20mooted%20by%20the%20Government%20in%202017%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20opposed%20the%20amendment%20and%20suggested%20that%20the%20Government%20reconsider%20its%20decision%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20it%20would%20open%20up%20the%20possibility%20of%20creating%20shell%20companies.%20The%20relevant%20portion%20of%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20ECI%20is%20reproduced%20below%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%9CCertain%20amendments%20have%20been%20proposed%20in%20Section%20182%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%2C%20where%20the%20first%20proviso%20has%20been%20omitted%20and%20consequently%20the%20limit%20of%20seven%20and%20a%20half%20percent%20(7.5%25)%20of%20the%20average%20net%20profits%20in%20the%20preceding%20three%20financial%20years%20on%20contributions%20by%20companies%20has%20been%20removed%20from%20the%20statute.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20opens%20up%20the%20possibility%20of%20shell%20companies%20being%20set%20up%20for%20the%20sole%20purpose%20of%20making%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20with%20no%20other%20business%20of%20consequence%20having%20disbursable%20profits.%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-primacy-vote-over-note%5C%22%3EThe%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Judgement%20Affirms%20the%20Primacy%20of%20the%20Vote%20Over%20the%20Note%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBonds%20issue%20could%20upstage%20pre-election%20issues%20and%20the%20broader%20narrative%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20indeed%20it%20is%20necessary%20to%20%E2%80%9Cidentify%20corruption%20and%20quid%20pro%20quo%20transactions%20in%20governance%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20if%20the%20contributions%20are%20%E2%80%9Cpurely%20business%20transactions%20made%20with%20the%20intent%20of%20securing%20benefits%20in%20return%E2%80%9D%2C%20then%20the%20data%20on%20donors%20and%20donees%20must%20be%20closely%20examined%20by%20all%20stakeholders%20of%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20the%20new%20government%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20post%20the%202024%20elections%2C%20the%20public%2C%20the%20media%20and%20most%20importantly%2C%20by%20the%20judiciary%20itself%20when%20the%20data%20is%20placed%20before%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnless%20the%20donors%E2%80%99%20identities%20are%20blocked%20through%20an%20ordinance%20or%20by%20a%20review%20petition%2C%20it%20would%20be%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%202014%20general%20elections%20that%20the%20electoral%20issues%20and%20narratives%20just%20before%20elections%20might%20be%20controlled%20not%20by%20Gujarat%20chief%20minister%2FPM%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20but%20by%20the%20potentially%20explosive%20fallout%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20direction%20to%20the%20SBI%20and%20the%20ECI%20to%20reveal%20who%20was%20funding%20political%20parties%2C%20especially%20the%20BJP%2C%20with%20the%20quid%20pro%20quo-tainted%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20has%20imputed%20knowledge%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20about%20who%20the%20donors%20were%20and%20are.%20So%20if%20indeed%20there%20are%20or%20were%20shell%20companies%20that%20were%20funnelling%20money%2Fblack%20money%20to%20political%20parties%2C%20the%20blame%20would%20squarely%20fall%20on%20the%20government%20or%20the%20ruling%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20data%20would%20indicate%20whether%20companies%20or%20persons%20being%20investigated%2C%20raided%20or%20prosecuted%20for%20corruption%2C%20money%20laundering%20and%20the%20like%20were%20donating%20money%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20at%20the%20Union%20government%20or%20in%20the%20states%2C%20and%20what%20happened%20after%20they%20donated%20or%20re-donated%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20would%20also%20indicate%20whether%20the%20companies%20that%20donated%20to%20opposition%20parties%20and%20not%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20were%20in%20any%20way%20targeted%20by%20states%20governments%20or%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20and%20what%2C%20if%20any%2C%20benefits%20especially%20accrued%20to%20companies%20that%20made%20large%20contributions%20to%20the%20ruling%20parties%20in%20the%20states%20and%20in%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20special%20interest%20would%20be%20contributions%20made%20by%20the%20print%20and%20electronic%20media%2C%20and%20if%20they%20did%2C%20the%20spotlight%20would%20be%20on%20them%20and%20on%20the%20credibility%20of%20their%20reporting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20short%2C%20issues%20like%20the%20Ram%20Temple%2C%20a%20uniform%20civil%20code%2C%20Article%20370%2C%20a%20five-trillion%20dollar%20economy%2C%20ration%20to%2080%20crore%20people%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20other%20welfare%20schemes%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20and%20issues%20like%20raging%20unemployment%2C%20farmers%E2%80%99%20distress%2C%20inflation%2C%20the%20alleged%20misuse%20of%20investigating%20agencies%20like%20the%20ED%2C%20CBI%20and%20Income%20Tax%20department%2C%20the%20alleged%20engineering%20of%20political%20defections%20through%20money%20power%20and%20Chinese%20aggression%20in%20Eastern%20Ladakh%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20could%20all%20be%20eclipsed%20by%20allegations%20and%20counter-allegations%20of%20a%20possible%20assault%20on%20democracy%20by%20opaque%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20not%20only%20by%20the%20BJP%2C%20but%20also%20by%20other%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FjBom6uGEMrE%3Fsi%3DNp4Dy1ek3f-gl146%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESitting%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20made%20avoidable%20adulatory%20statements%20about%20PM%20Modi%2C%20such%20as%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20proud%20and%20privileged%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20function%20to%20celebrate%20%5Bthe%5D%20diamond%20jubilee%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20Gujarat%20High%20Court%20and%20that%20too%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20our%20most%20popular%2C%20loved%2C%20vibrant%20and%20visionary%20leader%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-judge-describes-modi-as-popular-vibrant-and-visionary-leader%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eby%20Justice%20M.R.%20Shah%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmodi-justice-arun-mishra%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%20is%20Justice%20Arun%20Mishra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20a%20responsible%20and%20most%20friendly%20member%20of%20the%20international%20community%20under%20the%20stewardship%20of%20internationally%20acclaimed%20visionary%20Prime%20Minister%20Shri%20Narendra%20Modi.%20We%20thank%20the%20versatile%20genius%20who%20thinks%20globally%20and%20acts%20globally%2C%20Shri%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20for%20his%20inspiring%20speech%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20number%20of%20decisions%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20government%20have%20raised%20eyebrows%2C%20not%20just%20of%20reputed%20senior%20advocates%20of%20the%20top%20court%2C%20but%20also%20of%20its%20eminent%20retired%20judges.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20itself%20had%20come%20under%20unprecedented%20attack%20by%20no%20less%20a%20person%20than%20a%20Union%20law%20minister%20and%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20India%2C%20not%20just%20because%20the%20apex%20court%20had%20set%20aside%20the%20National%20Judicial%20Appointments%20Commission%2C%20but%20also%20because%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20exercising%20the%20power%20of%20judicial%20review!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20January%2011%2C%202023%2C%20Vice%20President%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20attacked%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20stand%20on%20the%20basic%20structure%20doctrine%2C%20on%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%20on%20its%20power%20of%20judicial%20review%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1890297%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20these%20words%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20democratic%20society%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98basic%E2%80%99%20of%20any%20%E2%80%98basic%20structure%E2%80%99%20has%20to%20be%20the%20supremacy%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20mandate%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20people.%20Thus%2C%20the%20primacy%20and%20sovereignty%20of%20parliament%20and%20legislature%20is%20inviolable%20%E2%80%A6%20The%20power%20of%20parliament%20to%20amend%20the%20constitution%20and%20deal%20with%20legislation%20is%20not%20subject%20to%20any%20other%20authority.%20This%20is%20%5Bthe%5D%20lifeline%20of%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20speech%20on%20January%2021%2C%202023%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20responded%20thus%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20like%20the%20North%20Star%2C%20guides%20and%20gives%20certain%20direction%20to%20the%20interpreters%20and%20implementers%20of%20the%20constitution%20when%20the%20path%20ahead%20is%20convoluted%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20basic%20structure%20or%20the%20philosophy%20of%20the%20constitution%20is%20premised%20on%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20separation%20of%20powers%2C%20judicial%20review%2C%20secularism%2C%20federalism%2C%20freedom%20and%20dignity%20of%20the%20individual%20and%20integrity%20of%20the%20nation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20last%20week%2C%20he%20along%20with%20his%20colleagues%20spoke%20from%20the%20bench%20and%2C%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20vice%20president%E2%80%99s%20remarks%2C%20was%20saying%20that%20the%20power%20of%20parliament%20to%20deal%20with%20legislation%20is%20subject%20to%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%20that%20amendments%20to%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%20Income%20Tax%20Act%20and%20Companies%20Act%20to%20accommodate%20the%20opaque%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20had%20breached%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20opacity%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20had%20clogged%20the%20lifeline%20of%20democracy%20by%20denying%20ordinary%20citizens%20the%20right%20to%20lift%20the%20veil%20of%20secrecy%20over%20the%20quid%20pro%20quo%20between%20corporates%20and%20the%20governments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20once%20again%20restored%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20faith%20in%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Frahul-singh%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERahul%20Singh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20former%20civil%20servant%20who%20retired%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%2C%20Government%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708938303000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F09172044%2FScreen-Shot-2021-03-09-at-5.20.25-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhumiliation-upending-poll-narratives-supreme-court-electoral-bonds-judgement%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Data%20revealed%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20and%20the%20Election%20Commission%20could%20reveal%20links%20between%20political%20donors%20and%20action%20by%20investigating%20agencies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20contributions%20made%20by%20the%20print%20and%20electronic%20media.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhumiliation-upending-poll-narratives-supreme-court-electoral-bonds-judgement%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IndiGo%20launches%20direct%20daily%20flights%20between%20Hyderabad%20and%20Bangkok%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708938145000%2C%22visual%2