not%20pay%20him%20gratuity.%20He%20does%20not%20have%20an%20employees%E2%80%99%20insurance%20corpus%20towards%20which%20a%20part%20of%20his%20salary%20goes.%20Mondal%2C%20thus%2C%20says%20that%20he%20does%20not%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20292px)%2085vw%2C%20292px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-746x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22292%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-746x1024.jpg%20746w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1.jpg%20874w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697965%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22401%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty.%20Photo%3A%20Intifada%20P.%20Basheer%20and%20Azam%20Abbas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20an%20accident%20happens%2C%20they%20won%E2%80%99t%20even%20help%20me%20get%20treatment%2C%20I%20think%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20jute%20mills%20of%20Bengal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20number%20of%20permanent%20workers%20engaged%20in%20the%20jute%20mills%20of%20Bengal%20%E2%80%93%20once%20a%20flourishing%20industry%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20on%20the%20decline%20for%20the%20past%2010%20years.%20The%20scores%20of%20workers%20whom%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%20in%20the%20district%20and%20outside%20say%20that%20out%20of%20permanent%2C%20special%20and%20temporary%20classes%20of%20workers%2C%20mill%20owners%20are%20keen%20on%20employing%20the%20most%20number%20of%20new%20people%20in%20the%20last%20category%20alone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20workers%20are%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9Czero%20number%E2%80%9D%20workers%20%E2%80%93%20their%20employment%20identity%20number%20is%20effectively%20zero%20because%20they%20are%20not%20registered%20with%20the%20mill.%20Such%20workers%20are%20often%20sent%20to%20mills%20by%20agencies%2C%20which%20are%20controlled%20by%20layers%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%2075%20out%20of%20104%20jute%20mills%20located%20in%20the%20state%2C%20Bengal%20is%20still%20the%20hub%20of%20the%20Indian%20jute%20industry%20valued%20at%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore.%20According%20to%20the%20Jute%20Commission%20of%20India%20records%2C%20as%20of%20December%2031%2C%202022%2C%20there%20are%20approximately%2046%2C487%20permanent%20workers%20and%201%2C08%2C461%20contractual%20workers%20working%20in%20the%20jute%20industry%20in%20India.%20However%2C%20beyond%20the%20record%20books%2C%20over%203%20lakh%20people%20are%20associated%20with%20the%20jute%20mills%20%E2%80%93%20unofficially.%20Two%20in%20three%20workers%20are%20working%20contractually%20in%20jobs%20that%20give%20little%20other%20than%20a%20basic%20income%20when%20there%20is%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBharat%20Ram%20says%20his%20grandfather%20left%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20came%20to%20the%20jute%20town%20of%20Bhatpara%20to%20work%20at%20a%20mill%20during%20the%20British%20rule.%20A%20third-generation%20jute%20mill%20worker%2C%20Bharat%20still%20works%20in%20the%20factory%20where%20his%20grandfather%20did.%20But%20he%20is%20one%20of%20the%20lucky%20few%20with%20a%20permanent%20job%20at%20the%20mill.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAlmost%20all%20jute%20mill%20workers%20stay%20in%20slums%20%E2%80%93%20which%20should%20give%20you%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20they%20are%20paid.%20Contractual%20workers%20get%20as%20low%20Rs%20200%20per%20day%20in%20some%20mills%2C%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20minimum%20wage%20for%20unskilled%20workers%20in%20Bengal.%20But%20officially%2C%20there%20is%20no%20record%20of%20most%20of%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bharat%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20was%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20different%20earlier%E2%80%9D%20and%20every%20worker%20was%20eligible%20for%20provident%20fund%20contributions%2C%20gratuity%2C%20and%20employees%E2%80%99%20state%20insurance%20benefits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShame%2C%20cleanliness%20%E2%80%98distant%E2%80%99%20concepts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHarendra%20Prasad%20Yadav%2C%20another%20generational%20jute%20mill%20worker%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20points%20to%20the%20rot%20in%20the%20system%20and%20claims%20that%20while%20news%20is%20made%20when%3Cspan%3E%20jute%20mills%20are%20closed%20due%20to%20workers%E2%80%99%20agitations%2C%20government%20incentives%20all%20go%20to%20the%20mill%20owners.%20%E2%80%9COur%20condition%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20improve%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20Retired%20for%20years%20now%2C%20Harendra%20is%20yet%20to%20receive%20his%20gratuity%20benefits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20269px)%2085vw%2C%20269px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112540%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM-885x1024.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22269%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112540%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM-885x1024.png%20885w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112540%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM-259x300.png%20259w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112540%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201037w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698861%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22311%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20gutter%20run%20through%20a%20workers%E2%80%99%20colony%20in%20Bhatpara%2C%20Bengal.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHarendra%20shares%20his%20quarters%20with%20his%20son%2C%20two%20grandsons%2C%20and%20a%20daughter-in-law.%20On%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20narrow%20lanes%20that%20lead%20to%20his%20house%2C%20there%20are%20rows%20of%20similar%20cramped%20rooms.%20A%20foul-smelling%20sewer%20gutter%20cleaves%20the%20alley%20in%20two.%20This%20is%20a%20playground%20for%20children%20by%20day%2C%20and%20a%20shared%20toilet%20by%20night.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20around%2060%2C000%20jute%20mill%20workers%20in%20the%20North%2024%20Parganas%20district%20alone.%20Nestled%20within%20the%20shadows%20of%20towering%20jute%20mills%20are%20the%20workers%E2%80%99%20colonies%20in%20which%20almost%20all%20of%20them%20live.%20Within%20each%20workers%E2%80%99%20colony%20is%20at%20most%20a%20single%20common%20bathroom%20without%20any%20doors%20or%20curtains.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Janki%20Ram%2C%20a%20mill%20worker%2C%20the%20Swachh%20Bharat%20Abhiyan%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20cleanliness%20drive%20%E2%80%93%20seems%20a%20distant%20dream.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20we%20have%20a%20ditch%20right%20at%20our%20doorstep%2C%20even%20the%20%5Bmosquito-borne%5D%20dengue%20is%20afraid%20to%20come%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20jokes%20Janki.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamli%20Devi%E2%80%99s%20son%20works%20at%20the%20factory.%20She%20says%20that%20for%20women%20in%20the%20colonies%20who%20struggle%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20single%20shared%20toilet%2C%20shame%20is%20distant%20concept%20too.%20%E2%80%9C%3Cspan%3EWe%20can%E2%80%99t%20even%20afford%20to%20raise%20your%20voice%20against%20the%20mill%20owner%2C%20otherwise%20we%20will%20be%20driven%20away%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20309px)%2085vw%2C%20309px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112429%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.33%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22309%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112429%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.33%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%20822w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112429%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.33%25E2%2580%25AFAM-260x300.png%20260w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698858%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22356%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20jute%20workers%E2%80%99%20colony.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorkers%20out%20of%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20local%20member%20of%20parliament%2C%20Arjun%20Singh%2C%20says%20that%20he%20has%20spoken%20to%20%3Cspan%3Emany%20jute%20mill%20owners%20about%20the%20problem%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20no%20one%20has%20done%20anything.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhatever%20allegations%20the%20workers%20are%20making%20are%20right.%20The%20condition%20of%20jute%20mill%20colonies%20is%20primitive.%20Jute%20mills%20never%20run%20at%20a%20loss.%20The%20owners%20usurp%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20workers%20from%20their%20provident%20fund%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Singh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESingh%2C%20known%20for%20his%20strong-arm%20tactics%20in%20the%20area%2C%20was%20a%20longtime%20Trinamool%20Congress%20leader%20but%20quit%20the%20party%20in%202019%20to%20win%20the%20Barrackpore%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%20as%20a%20BJP%20candidate.%20In%202022%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20his%20former%20party%20over%20the%20jute%20price-cap%20issue%20which%20led%20to%20the%20closure%20of%20about%20a%20dozen%20mills%20sending%20more%20than%2060%2C000%20workers%20out%20of%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20majority%20of%20voters%20in%20the%20Barrackpore%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%20belonging%20to%20the%20working%20class%2C%20jute%20is%20an%20evocative%20issue%20that%20no%20political%20party%20can%20overlook.%20In%20its%20prime%2C%20the%20jute%20belt%20encompassing%20North%2024%20Parganas%2C%20Hooghly%2C%20and%20Howrah%20attracted%20thousands%20of%20workers%20from%20Bihar%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20However%2C%20a%20considerable%20number%20have%20since%20returned%2C%20with%20hundreds%20of%20local%20labourers%20either%20choosing%20low-skill%20jobs%20or%20migrating%20to%20other%20states%20in%20pursuit%20of%20employment%20opportunities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJiten%20Majhi%2C%20who%20used%20to%20be%20a%20worker%20at%20a%20closed%20mill%2C%20is%20all%20set%20to%20move%20to%20south%20India%20for%20better%20opportunities.%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EBhai%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20situation%20in%20Bengal%20has%20changed%20completely.%20We%20used%20to%20consider%20this%20place%20as%20one%20we%20could%20live%20out%20our%20futures%20in%20simply%20for%20the%20work%20opportunities%20it%20provided%2C%20but%20now%20there%20is%20not%20much%20hope%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jiten%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20413px)%2085vw%2C%20413px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112408%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.44%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x985.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22413%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112408%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.44%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x985.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112408%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.44%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x289.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112408%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.44%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201110w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698857%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22397%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJute%20bags.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrice%20and%20fall%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Bengal%20and%20union%20government%2C%20in%20a%20tripartite%20agreement%20with%20jute%20industry%20representatives%20and%20labour%20unions%2C%20revised%20the%20minimum%20daily%20wage%20for%20entry-level%20labourers%20from%20Rs%20370%20to%20Rs%20485.%20The%20revision%20came%20after%20five%20years%20but%20did%20not%20fulfil%20the%20demands%20of%20a%20minimum%20monthly%20wage%20of%20Rs%2026%2C000%2C%20the%20inclusion%20of%20all%20workers%20in%20the%20master%20roll%2C%20and%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20system%20which%20would%20only%20have%20permanent%20and%20special%20%3Cem%3Ebadlee%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20transferrable%2C%20workers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20jute%20industry%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%20The%20government%20does%20not%20have%20the%20willingness%20to%20do%20anything.%20However%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20able%20to%20give%20it%20the%20required%20importance.%20In%20my%20opinion%2C%20there%20should%20be%20a%20workers%E2%80%99%20movement%20against%20the%20gross%20neglect%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20former%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20MP%20and%20trade%20union%20leader%20Taritbaran%20Topdar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJute%20is%20primarily%20procured%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20food%20grain%20packaging.%20A%20government%20regulation%20mandates%20100%25%20jute%20bag%20usage%20for%20food%20grains%20and%2020%25%20for%20sugar.%20However%2C%20current%20government%20orders%20for%20jute%20bags%20(1.48%20lakh%20bales%20in%20October-November)%20fell%20short%20of%20the%20previous%20volumes%20(3.50%20lakh%20bales).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112347%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x703.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112347%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x703.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112347%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x206.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112347%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201104w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698856%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22577%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJute%20workers%20at%20a%20factory.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CDue%20to%20the%20high%20demand%20for%20wheat%2C%20farmers%20are%20selling%20through%20the%20open%20market%2C%20thus%20reducing%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20need%20for%20jute%20bags%20for%20food%20grain%20storage.%20That%20is%20why%20despite%20a%20bumper%20crop%2C%20farmers%20are%20struggling%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Raghavendra%20Gupta%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20Indian%20Jute%20Mills%20Association.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESynthetic%20bags%20have%20also%20flooded%20the%20market%2C%20alleges%20%3Cspan%3ERitabrata%20Banerjee%2C%20state%20president%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Trade%20Union%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20effort%20has%20been%20on%20for%20decades.%20Now%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20bring%20in%20a%20new%20variety%20called%20poly-jute%20which%20is%20also%20said%20to%20be%20environmentally%20friendly.%20A%20section%20of%20businessmen%20from%20western%20India%20is%20exerting%20influence%20on%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20this%20regard.%20The%20jute%20industry%20is%20not%20only%20suffering%20from%20the%20lack%20of%20action%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20but%20also%20from%20wrong%20policies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Banerjee%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20has%20set%20a%20minimum%20support%20price%20of%20Rs%205%2C400%20per%20quintal%20for%20jute%20in%20the%20current%20year.%20However%2C%20reports%20indicate%20that%20farmers%20are%20often%20receiving%20less%2C%20averaging%20around%20Rs%204%2C200%20or%20Rs%204%2C500%20per%20quintal%2C%20with%20prices%20falling%20even%20lower%20in%20some%20areas.%20While%20the%20number%20licensed%20warehouses%20authorised%20to%20buy%20and%20store%20jute%20stand%20at%206%2C000%2C%20the%20number%20of%20unlicensed%20entities%20engaging%20in%20direct%20jute%20purchases%20from%20warehouses%20has%20reportedly%20risen%20above%2032%2C000%20in%20the%20current%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20frustration%20of%20the%20farmers%20is%20palpable.%20Sanuallah%2C%20a%20jute%20cultivator%20from%20Cooch%20Behar%2C%20expressed%20the%20challenge%20of%20finding%20fair%20prices%20after%20years%20of%20dependence%20on%20the%20crop.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20years%2C%20we%20have%20poured%20our%20sweat%20and%20toil%20into%20this%20crop.%20With%20current%20prices%2C%20the%20future%20of%20this%20cultivation%20remains%20uncertain%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESamar%20Biswas%2C%20a%20jute%20farmer%20from%20Karimpur%20in%20Nadia%20district%20echoes%20the%20same%20sentiment.%20%E2%80%9CDelhi%E2%80%99s%20orders%20have%20been%20slashed%2C%20so%20mill%20owners%20are%20now%20forcing%20us%20to%20sell%20our%20produce%20at%20Rs%202%2C500%20or%20face%20dire%20consequences.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Biswas%20voted%20for%20BJP%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%202021%20assembly%20elections%2C%20but%20the%20issue%20of%20fair%20prices%20resonates%20across%20political%20allegiances.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20may%20remain%20loyal%20to%20Modi%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20loyalty%20cannot%20sustain%20empty%20stomachs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708927715000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112616%2FUntitled-design-1-5.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fjute-mills-bengal-labour-india-out-of-work%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%2075%20out%20of%20104%20of%20India's%20jute%20mills%20located%20in%20the%20state%2C%20Bengal%20is%20still%20the%20hub%20of%20the%20Indian%20jute%20industry%2C%20valued%20at%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore.%20However%2C%20its%20workers%20are%20perpetually%20at%20a%20disadvantage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fjute-mills-bengal-labour-india-out-of-work%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20RBI%2C%20rivals%20PhonePe%2C%20PineLabs%20have%20said%20about%20the%20Paytm%20crisis%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708927141000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108001332%2Cimgsize-1254369.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Frbi-phonepe-and-pinelabs-on-the-paytm-crisis%2Farticleshow%2F108001350.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20RBI%20directed%20Paytm%20Payment%20Bank%20to%20stop%20accepting%20deposits%20and%20credit%20transactions%20after%20March%2015%20due%20to%20non-compliance.%20PhonePe's%20CEO%20mentioned%20there%20was%20ample%20time%20for%20Paytm%20to%20respond.%20PineLabs%20emphasized%20trust%20cannot%20be%20bought.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Frbi-phonepe-and-pinelabs-on-the-paytm-crisis%2Farticleshow%2F108001350.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Kashmiri%20Sapphires%20Set%20To%20Dazzle%20The%20World%20Again%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20decade%20after%20a%2019.88-carat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhunt-for-stolen-kashmir-sapphire-takes-mysterious-turn-1267415%5C%22%3EKashmir%20sapphire%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frare-kashmir-sapphire-fetches-rs-2-8-crore-at-us-auction-483035%5C%22%3Eshattered%20auction%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Geneva%2C%20the%20potential%20return%20of%20the%20priceless%20gems%20from%20the%20strife-torn%20region%20to%20global%20markets%20is%20on%20the%20horizon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cushion-shaped%20sapphire%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Star%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20surprised%20buyers%20in%202013%20with%20a%20sale%20price%20of%20nearly%20%243%2C483%2C017%20(approximately%20Rs%2020%20crore).%20Now%2C%20officials%20claim%20that%20more%20peacock%20blue-coloured%20sapphires%20will%20be%20mined%20in%20the%20Paddar%20region%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20inhospitable%20terrains%20in%20the%20bordering%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2Febl152bo_sapphire-gemstone-is-the-best-for-these-zodiac-signs-know-about-them_625x300_02_March_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E(Photo%20for%20representation)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcolonial-era-file-sheds-light-on-indian-gems-and-jewels-in-uks-royal-treasury-3928509%5C%22%3EKashmir%20sapphires%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20revered%20as%20among%20the%20finest%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20resurgence%20in%20the%20Kashmiri%20economy%20marks%20a%20significant%20shift%2C%20seemingly%20overcoming%20longstanding%20hurdles%20related%20to%20mining%20and%20marketing%20rights.%20It's%20reliably%20learned%20that%20local%20traders%2C%20previously%20resistant%20to%20outsider%20involvement%20in%20mining%20and%20marketing%20the%20gems%2C%20had%20persistently%20demanded%20exorbitant%20prices%2C%20hindering%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20landscape%20is%20evolving.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20pivotal%20moment%20for%20these%20sapphires%20came%20after%20traders%20from%20Kashmir%20were%20advised%20by%20the%20state-owned%20Gems%20and%20Jewellery%20Export%20Promotion%20Council%20(GJEPC)%20to%20adhere%20to%20global%20trade%20norms.%20In%20essence%2C%20they%20were%20advised%20to%20auction%20the%20gems%2C%20mirroring%20the%20international%20diamond%20trade%2C%20and%20evaluate%20offers%20from%20buyers.%20The%20traders%20have%20since%20embraced%20this%20guidance%2C%20which%20emanated%20from%20the%20Commerce%20Ministry%20through%20the%20GJEPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CKashmir%20sapphires%20are%20very%20unique.%20Mining%20and%20trading%20of%20these%20gems%20need%20to%20be%20streamlined%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sabyasachi%20Ray%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20GJEPC.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20explained%20to%20those%20involved%20with%20the%20trading%20of%20sapphires%20the%20importance%20of%20doing%20the%20business%20methodically%20and%20as%20per%20international%20norms.%20The%20traders%20should%20not%20be%20raising%20unrealistic%20demands%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EKashmir's%20Tryst%20With%20Gems%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20implementing%20such%20measures%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20India's%20most%20troubled%20state%20bordering%20Pakistan%2C%20poses%20considerable%20challenges.%20The%20allure%20of%20gems%20has%20historically%20captivated%20tribes%20spanning%20the%20vast%20stretch%20between%20Afghanistan%20and%20Kashmir.%20Gemstones%20have%20long%20been%20understood%20as%20transformative%20assets%20by%20tribal%20communities%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20Pakistan.%20GJEPC%20officials%20caution%20that%20Kashmiri%20traders%20could%20still%20resist%20conforming%20to%20international%20guidelines%2C%20potentially%20reverting%20to%20old%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecognising%20the%20sensitivity%20surrounding%20gem%20trade%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20GJEPC%20is%20diligently%20navigating%20these%20complexities%2C%20cognisant%20of%20the%20pivotal%20role%20local%20traders%20play.%20The%20Himalayan%20region's%20gems%20boast%20a%20rich%20historical%20lineage%2C%20extending%20from%20India%20to%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsider%20Afghanistan's%20gem%20mining%20heritage%2C%20which%20dates%20back%20approximately%202%2C300%20years%20to%20the%20era%20of%20Alexander%20the%20Great.%20By%20the%2010th%20century%2C%20the%20gem%20mines%20of%20northern%20and%20eastern%20Afghanistan%2C%20bordering%20Tajikistan%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20were%20famed%20for%20their%20rubies%2C%20sapphires%2C%20tourmaline%2C%20lapis%20lazuli%2C%20and%20topaz.%20Today%2C%20gem%20mines%20in%20northeastern%20Afghan%20provinces%20serve%20as%20revenue%20sources%20for%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%20Similarly%2C%20in%20neighbouring%20Pakistan%2C%20gem%20mining%20and%20trade%20remain%20contentious%2C%20often%20sparking%20tensions%20over%20the%20extraction%20of%20high-value%20gemstones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EA%20Determined%20Government%20To%20Go%20Ahead%20With%20Mining%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20is%20determined%20to%20avoid%20such%20controversies%20in%20Kashmir.%20The%20government%2C%20specifically%20the%20Commerce%20Ministry%2C%20has%20set%20up%20a%20detailed%20roadmap%20for%20mining%20sapphires%20from%20Kashmir.%20A%20preliminary%20survey%20for%20the%20sapphire%20mines%20in%20the%20Paddar%20region%20has%20been%20completed%20by%20the%20Geological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(GSI).%20Now%2C%20there%20will%20be%20scientific%20exploration%20of%20the%20area.%20Extreme%20geographical%20conditions%20and%20lack%20of%20resources%20have%20hampered%20the%20commercial%20exploitation%20of%20this%20valuable%20stone.%20The%20status%20of%20the%20preliminary%20survey%20was%20discussed%20by%20top%20officials%20at%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20board%20of%20directors%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Minerals%20Limited%20here%2C%20chaired%20by%20the%20state's%20chief%20secretary%20Arun%20Mehta.%20A%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20some%20of%20the%20sapphires%20were%20taken%20to%20Jaipur%20for%20display%20at%20an%20exhibition%20where%20the%20Kashmir%20sapphires%20generated%20tremendous%20interest%20among%20the%20traders%20of%20the%20desert%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20top%20official%20of%20the%20state%20told%20this%20reporter%20the%20Kashmir%20stones%20are%20considered%20unique%20across%20the%20world%2C%20even%20better%20than%20the%20ones%20found%20in%20Mogok%2C%20Myanmar.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Kashmir%20sapphires%20are%20the%20best%20in%20the%20world%20and%20we%20will%20be%20seeking%20the%20best%20price%20for%20them.%20Plans%20for%20mining%20are%20firmly%20in%20place%2C%E2%80%9D%20Arun%20Kishore%20Kotwal%2C%20a%20top%20official%20of%20the%20mining%20department%20in%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%2C%20said%20in%20a%20telephonic%20interview.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKotwal%20said%20the%20Kashmir%20blue%20peacock-coloured%20sapphires%20are%20in%20limited%20quantities%20and%20will%20be%20produced%20in%20phases.%20The%20total%20amount%20of%20sapphires%20to%20be%20mined%20would%20be%20in%20the%20region%20of%20Rs%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22tel%3A3000-4000%5C%22%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%2C000-4%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0crore.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20then%20we%20will%20work%20on%20the%20next%20phase%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kotwal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJKML%2C%20it%20has%20been%20reliably%20learnt%2C%20has%20awarded%20the%20exploration%20of%20sapphire%20mines%20to%20Mineworks%2C%20a%20Delhi-based%20company.%20Mineworks%20will%20jointly%20execute%20the%20project%20with%20JKML.%20The%20move%2C%20however%2C%20has%20triggered%20some%20anger%20among%20the%20business%20community%20in%20Kishtwar%2C%20which%20did%20not%20like%20an%20%E2%80%9Coutsider%E2%80%9D%20being%20granted%20the%20contract.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Mineworks%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20affected.%20Managed%20by%20the%20Tongya%20family%2C%20the%20company%20is%20among%20the%20top%20Indian%20gems%20companies%20with%20footprints%20across%20the%20world.%20Recently%2C%20one%20of%20its%20subsidiaries%20acquired%20an%20extremely%20rare%2C%20high-quality%20Zambian%20emerald%20that%20was%20sold%20at%20an%20auction%20in%20Lusaka%20for%20an%20undisclosed%20amount.%20The%20gemstone%2C%20gorgeously%20green%20and%20wonderfully%20translucent%2C%20was%20christened%20Insofu%2C%20which%20means%20'baby%20elephant'%20in%20the%20local%20Bemba%20language%20of%20Zambia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%206%2C100%20carats%20and%201%2C220%20gm%2C%20the%20gem%20is%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20emeralds%20to%20be%20mined%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20specialises%20in%20blue%20sapphires%2C%20boasting%20fascinating%20collections%20of%20blue-coloured%20stones%2C%20among%20them%20two%20rare%2C%20flawless%20oval-shaped%20sapphires%20%E2%80%94%20called%20the%20Sunburst%20Sapphires%20%E2%80%94%20weighing%20151.15%20carat%20and%20127.68%20carat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20All%20Are%20Satisfied%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20everyone%20in%20the%20state%20is%20happy%20with%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20state%20government%20to%20collaborate%20with%20a%20Delhi-based%20company.%20The%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Industries%20and%20Commerce%20Department%20feels%20that%20JKML%20could%20have%20avoided%20the%20joint%20venture%20and%20done%20the%20mining%20on%20its%20own.%20Other%20business%20associations%20in%20the%20state%20have%20also%20expressed%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20agreement.%20Commerce%20Ministry%20officials%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20such%20fears%20from%20the%20state%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20acknowledges%20the%20importance%20and%20class%20of%20these%20gems.%20Market%20experts%20say%20Asia%20has%20some%20of%20the%20best%20gems%20across%20the%20world%2C%20with%20Kashmir%20leading%20in%20peacock%20blue%20sapphires%2C%20followed%20by%20Myanmar%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Thailand%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20Cambodia%2C%20Madagascar%2C%20and%20Australia.%20The%20Kashmir%20sapphire%2C%20claim%20experts%2C%20displays%20a%20unique%20character%20that%20signifies%20the%20most%20desirable%20and%20expensive%20of%20gems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Landslide%20And%20A%20Treasure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20wanted%20to%20take%20charge%20of%20the%20princely%20state%20of%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%2C%20but%20their%20attempts%20were%20thwarted%20by%20the%20then%20Maharaja%20Ranbir%20Singh%2C%20who%20was%20loyal%20to%20the%20empire%20but%20denied%20them%20authoritative%20privileges%20over%20his%20land%20and%20people.%20Interestingly%2C%20four%20years%20before%20the%20Maharaja's%20death%20in%201881%2C%20a%20landslide%20occurred%20in%20a%20harsh%20and%20remote%20cirque%20valley%20of%20the%20Zanskar%20range.%20At%2013%2C000%20feet%20above%20sea%20level%2C%20the%20landslip%20exposed%20a%20100-feet%20wide%20area%20of%20pegmatitic%20rock%20with%20blue%20crystals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sapphires%20were%20first%20traced%20in%201881%20by%20some%20local%20traders%20who%20lived%20in%20the%20valleys%20of%20Zanskar%20and%20Lahul.%20They%20traded%20the%20gems%20for%20salt.%20By%201882%2C%20parcels%20of%20blue%20gemstones%20began%20to%20reach%20Delhi%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20across%20India.%20The%20Maharaja%20became%20extremely%20concerned%20about%20the%20lost%20fortune%20and%20immediately%20ordered%20his%20army%20of%20soldiers%20to%20guard%20the%20mines.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20British%20government%20took%20charge%20of%20the%20mines.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20original%20old%20mine%2C%20which%20produced%20a%20limited%20assortment%20of%20high-quality%20and%20large-size%20Kashmir%20sapphires%2C%20was%20entirely%20depleted%20in%201888.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20some%20of%20the%20gems%20were%20traded%20at%20the%20marketing%20centres%20of%20Kullu%20and%20Shimla%20by%20a%20syndicate%20of%20jewellers.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20Geological%20Survey%20of%20India%20concurred%20with%20the%20discovery%20of%20sapphires%20in%20a%20glacial%20cirque%20above%20the%20village%20of%20Sumjam%2C%20on%20the%20southwest%20slopes%20of%20the%20rugged%20Zanskar%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Commerce%20Ministry's%20Intervention%20Is%20Timely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20work%20of%20exploration%20and%20security%20of%20mineral%20wealth%20and%20assets%20is%20looked%20after%20by%20the%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20Mineral%20Limited.%20There%20have%20been%20occasions%20when%20the%20operations%20of%20JKML%20have%20drawn%20flak%20from%20local%20traders%2C%20many%20even%20alleging%20that%20it%20undertook%20mining%20operations%20but%20there%20was%20no%20clarity%20about%20the%20collection%20of%20the%20gems.%20As%20per%20rules%2C%20the%20mining%20operation%20needs%20to%20be%20completed%20between%20July%201%20and%20September%2018%2C%202024.%20Thereafter%2C%20the%20gems%20will%20be%20sent%20for%20processing%20into%20finished%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Commerce%20Ministry's%20intervention%20is%20both%20crucial%20and%20timely%20because%20there%20have%20been%20occasions%20when%20the%20exposed%20mineral%20wealth%20was%20stolen%20by%20smugglers.%20Now%2C%20the%20ministry%20hopes%20its%20intervention%20and%20that%20of%20the%20state%20government%20will%20stop%20such%20smuggling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjay%C2%A0Kumar%2C%20SP%20Kishtwar%2C%20has%20clarified%20recently%20to%20mediapersons%20that%20there%20were%20a%20few%20reports%20of%20smuggling%2C%20but%20it%20has%20stopped.%20A%20few%20smugglers%20have%20been%20booked%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20the%20mines%20are%20buried%20under%20ten%20feet%20of%20snow.%20And%20there%20is%20high%20security.%20Once%20the%20area%20opens%20up%20by%20the%20end%20of%20May%2C%20mining%20will%20start.%20And%20then%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20top-class%20sapphires%20will%20make%20its%20way%20to%20the%20Indian%20and%20global%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Shantanu%20Guha%20Ray%20is%20the%20Asia%20Editor%20of%20Central%20News%20Agency.%20His%20book%20'The%20Diamond%20Trial'%20came%20out%20in%202019).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708926900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2Febl152bo_sapphire-gemstone-is-the-best-for-these-zodiac-signs-know-about-them_625x300_02_March_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fkashmiri-sapphires-set-to-dazzle-the-world-yet-again-5128759%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20decade%20after%20a%2019.88-carat%20Kashmir%20sapphire%20shattered%20auction%20records%20in%20Geneva%2C%20the%20potential%20return%20of%20the%20priceless%20gems%20from%20the%20strife-torn%20region%20to%20global%20markets%20is%20on%20the%20horizon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fkashmiri-sapphires-set-to-dazzle-the-world-yet-again-5128759%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fkashmiri-sapphires-set-to-dazzle-the-world-yet-again-5128759%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fkashmiri-sapphires-set-to-dazzle-the-world-yet-again-5128759%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hindu%20'puja'%20to%20continue%20in%20Gyanvapi%20cellar%3A%20Allahabad%20HC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A