find%20it%2C%20you%20have%20to%20keep%20at%20it.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EFreedom%20of%20speech%2C%20but%20also%20freedom%20after%20speech.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20green%2C%20he%20once%20said%20to%20me%2C%20twenty-five%20summers%20young%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20full%20of%20heart.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EDo%20not%20lose%20heart%2C%20he%20said%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20ocean%20is%20turbulent%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EDo%20not%20lose%20faith.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBlessed%20with%20principle%2C%20but%20also%20someone%20who%20knew%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20to%20laugh.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWho%20enjoyed%20a%20joke%20like%20no%20tomorrow.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOld%20lawyers%20don%E2%80%99t%20fade%20away%2C%20he%20said%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20just%20lose%20their%20appeal.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20understood%2C%20how%20things%20pass%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20time%20makes%20way%20for%20no%20one%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20that%20page%20had%20to%20be%20written%2C%20and%20that%20argument%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHad%20to%20be%20chiseled%20to%20perfection.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20liked%20the%20pen%20and%20signed%20his%20letters%2C%20to%20old%20and%20young%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESimply%20Fali.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmlanjyoti%20Goswami%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3ERiver%20Wedding%20(2019)%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3EVital%20Signs%20(2022)%3Cem%3E%2C%20published%20by%20Poetrywala.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708855241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25144137%2Ffa9d4329-08a7-4ec5-b1b2-d481c96bf277.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fa-poem-in-honour-of-fali-nariman%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eminent%20jurist%20and%20senior%20advocate%20Fali%20S.%20Nariman%20passed%20away%20at%20the%20age%20of%2095.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fa-poem-in-honour-of-fali-nariman%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Consumption%20Expenditure%20Released%20After%2011-Year%20Gap%20Highlights%20Persisting%20Inequality%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25145200%2Fstreet-175277_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20poorest%205%25%20of%20India%20spend%20merely%20an%20average%20of%20Rs%2046%20daily%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20Rs%2067%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20as%20against%20the%20richest%205%25%20whose%20daily%20consumption%20is%20Rs%20350%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20Rs%20700%20in%20urban%20parts%2C%20indicating%20a%20huge%20inequality%20in%20incomes%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Household%20Consumption%20Expenditure%20Survey%202022-23%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20released%20after%20a%20gap%20of%2011%20years%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20bottom%205%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20rural%20population%2C%20ranked%20by%20MPCE%20(monthly%20per%20capita%20consumption%20expenditure)%2C%20has%20an%20average%20MPCE%20of%20%E2%82%B91%2C373%20while%20it%20is%20%E2%82%B92%2C001%20for%20the%20same%20category%20of%20population%20in%20the%20urban%20areas.%20The%20top%205%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20rural%20and%20urban%20population%2C%20ranked%20by%20MPCE%2C%20has%20an%20average%20MPCE%20of%20%E2%82%B910%2C501%20and%20%E2%82%B920%2C824%2C%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20factsheet%20on%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20survey%2C%20released%20by%20the%20the%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%20Ministry%20on%20February%2024%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fthesundaystandard%2F2024%2FFeb%2F25%2Frs-46-per-person-consumption-a-day-by-poorest%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNEW%2520DELHI%2520%253A%2520The%2520poorest%25205%2CExpenditure%2520Survey%25202022%252D23%2520shows.%5C%22%3Ereleased%20the%20broad%20findings%20of%20the%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20carried%20out%20between%20August%202022%20and%20July%202023.%20The%20survey%20is%20usually%20conducted%20by%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Office%20every%20five%20years%20but%20the%20last%20report%20based%20on%20the%20survey%20in%202017-18%20after%20demonetisation%20and%20implementation%20of%20the%20the%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20(GST)%20was%20not%20released.%20The%20government%20cited%20%E2%80%9Cdata%20quality%E2%80%9D%20issues%20to%20stop%20its%20release.%20The%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20has%20been%20criticised%20for%20not%20collecting%20and%20sharing%20proper%20data%20on%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20report%20showed%20that%20although%20the%20average%20MPCE%20in%20urban%20households%20rose%20to%20Rs%203%2C510%20%E2%80%93%20an%20increase%20by%2033.5%25%20since%202011-12%20%E2%80%93%20and%20rural%20households%20to%20Rs%202008%20that%20is%20a%2040-42%25%20uptick%2C%20the%20jump%20is%20more%20owing%20to%20steep%20inflationary%20trends%20than%20any%20real%20rise%20in%20incomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20is%20proven%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20survey%20also%20revealed%20that%20the%20proportion%20of%20spending%20on%20food%20slid%20to%2046.4%25%20from%2052.9%25%20in%202011-12%20in%20rural%20households%2C%20while%20it%20dropped%20from%2042.6%25%20to%2039.2%25%20in%20the%20corresponding%20period%20for%20urban%20households.%20The%20figure%20could%20imply%20that%20people%20may%20be%20cutting%20down%20on%20spending%20on%20food%20because%20of%20high%20retail%20inflation%2C%20or%20have%20been%20relieved%20by%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20free%20ration%20scheme%20to%2080%20crore%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MPCE%20figures%20are%20based%20on%20data%20collected%20from%202%2C61%2C746%20households%2C%20of%20which%201%2C55%2C014%20were%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20spread%20over%20all%20States%20and%20Union%20Territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20MPCE%20numbers%20cited%20above%20do%20not%20take%20into%20account%20the%20imputed%20values%20of%20items%20received%20free%20of%20cost%20by%20individuals%20through%20various%20social%20welfare%20programmes%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fdistribution-of-5-kg-foodgrains-to-poor-under-pmgkay-extended-for-5-years-anurag-thakur%2Farticle67586389.ece%5C%22%3EPM%20Garib%20Kalyan%20Ann%20Yojana%20(PMGKAY)%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20State-run%20schemes%2C%20which%20were%20calculated%20separately%2C%20while%20including%20a%20few%20non-food%20items%20received%20through%20such%20schemes%2C%20including%20computers%2C%20mobile%20phones%2C%20bicycles%2C%20and%20clothing%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2FEconomy%2Fgovernment-puts-household-spending-report-on-hold%2Farticle61611660.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20average%20MPCE%2C%20at%202011-12%20prices%2C%20was%20a%20tad%20higher%20when%20these%20items%20were%20included%20while%20excluding%20free%20education%20and%20healthcare%20sops%20%E2%80%94%20at%20%E2%82%B92%2C054%20for%20rural%20households%2C%20and%20%E2%82%B93%2C544%20for%20urban%20homes%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESikkim%E2%80%99s%20MPCE%20is%20the%20highest%20among%20Indian%20states%20at%20Rs%207%2C731%20in%20rural%20and%20Rs%2012%2C%20105%20in%20urban%20households.%20Chhattisgarh%20was%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20ladder%20where%20the%20MPCE%20is%20Rs%202%2C466%20for%20rural%20and%20Rs%204%2C483%20for%20urban%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708853413000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25145200%2Fstreet-175277_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fconsumption-expenditure-released-after-11-year-gap-highlights-persisting-inequality%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20report%20showed%20that%20although%20the%20average%20MPCE%20in%20urban%20households%20rose%20to%20Rs%203%2C510%20%E2%80%93%20an%20increase%20by%2033.5%25%20since%202011-12%20%E2%80%93%20and%20rural%20households%20to%20Rs%202008%20that%20is%20a%2040-42%25%20uptick%2C%20the%20jump%20is%20more%20owing%20to%20steep%20inflationary%20trends%20than%20any%20real%20rise%20in%20incomes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fconsumption-expenditure-released-after-11-year-gap-highlights-persisting-inequality%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stories%20That%20Unveil%20the%20Many%20Worlds%20in%20Kerala%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25144446%2Fgaurav-kumar-33Z4FsBTiAY-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20increasing%20availability%20of%20the%20literatures%20of%20many%20distinct%20regions%20is%20one%20of%20the%20achievement%20of%20contemporary%20Indian%20publishing.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20%3Cem%3EFeeling%20Kerala%3A%20An%20Anthology%20of%20Contemporary%20Malayalam%20Stories%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20translated%20by%20J.%20Devika%20(Penguin%2C%202023)%20is%20a%20notable%20contribution.%20The%20stories%20cover%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20themes%20as%20may%20be%20expected%20from%20a%20mature%20literary%20ethos%20%E2%80%93%20migration%2C%20ecology%2C%20social%20friction%2C%20marital%20and%20familial%20discord%2C%20political%20and%20spiritual%20entrepreneurship%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20And%20few%20translators%20in%20the%20present%20have%20accomplished%20as%20much%20as%20Devika%20in%20the%20sheer%20quality%20and%20quantum%20of%20translations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDevika%E2%80%99s%20introduction%20to%20the%20overall%20volume%2C%20and%20smaller%20introductions%20to%20each%20story%2C%20though%20occasionally%20polemical%2C%20gives%20us%20a%20helpful%20initial%20handle.%20The%20anthology%20succeeds%20also%20as%20the%20short%20story%20is%20a%20particularly%20favoured%20genre%20in%20India.%20The%20short%20story%20is%20not%20a%20miniature%20novel%2C%20but%20rather%20often%20captures%20the%20entirety%20of%20a%20sentiment%2C%20one%20complete%20in%20itself%2C%20and%20one%20that%20invites%20the%20reader%20to%20a%20stilled%20and%20concentrated%20contemplation.%20Many%20of%20these%20stories%20are%20worth%20re-reading%2C%20and%20often%20require%20that%20second%20reading%20to%20fully%20unpack.%20One%20cannot%20hope%20to%20summarise%20all%20the%2013%20stories%2C%20but%20a%20description%20of%20a%20few%20will%20give%20a%20flavour%20of%20the%20wealth%20of%20the%20book%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20272px)%2085vw%2C%20272px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25144241%2FB038273S.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22272%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25144241%2FB038273S.jpeg%20400w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25144241%2FB038273S-200x300.jpeg%20200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698772%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22409%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFeeling%20Kerala%3A%20An%20Anthology%20of%20Contemporary%20Malayalam%20Stories%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ETranslated%20by%20J.%20Devika%3Cbr%3EPenguin%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYama%E2%80%99s%20story%20captures%20the%20bleak%20frustration%20and%20rage%20of%20a%20young%20woman%3A%20%E2%80%9Cshe%20had%20stored%20away%20pieces%20of%20lead%20from%20pencil%20stubs%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20ending%20her%20life%E2%80%A6%20as%20a%20child%2C%20she%20thought%20that%20all%20buses%20ran%20on%20towards%20the%20ever-receding%20horizon%E2%80%9D.%20She%20is%20trapped%20by%20a%20complaining%20mother%20and%20a%20school%20dropout%20brother%20ever%20hovering%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20criminality.%20Events%20unfold%20in%20a%20blur%20%E2%80%93%20her%20brother%2C%20perhaps%20inadvertently%2C%20kills%20the%20mother%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20steal%20her%20last%20piece%20of%20jewellery.%20The%20blur%20continues%20with%20the%20police%20arriving%2C%20the%20brother%20fleeing%2C%20and%20the%20protagonist%20needing%20to%20seek%20urgent%20employment%20to%20stave%20off%20hunger%20and%20isolation.%20Over%20the%20following%20weeks%20she%20keep%20hallucinating%20both%20her%20brother%E2%80%99s%20face%2C%20and%20her%20dead%20mother%20returning%20to%20demand%20her%20stolen%20gold.%20There%20are%20recurring%20surreal%20images%20of%20thefts%20at%20night%20%E2%80%93%20gold%20under%20a%20distant%20palm%20tree%20under%20a%20dark%20sky%E2%80%99s%20moon%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%20is%20not%20always%20clear%20what%20is%20real%20and%20what%20imagined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomething%20of%20that%20female%20frustration%20and%20anger%20is%20also%20present%20in%20the%20last%20story%20by%20Shahina.%20A%20single%20street%20and%20lane%20(Street%20No.%2010%2C%20Mangala%20Lane)%20is%20used%20to%20connect%20diverse%20stories%20of%20harassment%20%E2%80%93%20within%20the%20home%20and%20bathroom%2C%20toward%20boys%20or%20girls%20scarce%20a%20decade%20old%2C%20in%20crowded%20public%20transport.%20The%20story%20ends%20with%20a%20fantasia%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cseemingly%20never-ending%20line%20of%20naked%20women%E2%80%A6not%20shrinking%20in%20shame%2C%20not%20crouching%E2%80%A6%20%5Bmoving%5D%20slowly%2C%20unhurriedly%2C%20leisurely.%20Like%20the%20wind%2C%20the%20sun%2C%20the%20leaves%20and%20flowers%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20wistful%20stories%20of%20melancholy%20%E2%80%93%20the%20large%20houses%20that%20dot%20the%20Kerala%20countryside%20often%20have%20a%20single%20older%20person%20in%20them%2C%20with%20all%20their%20family%20scattered%20in%20distant%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20Kerala%20anticipates%20presciently%20so%20many%20of%20the%20problems%20India%20will%20inherit%20soon%20enough%20%E2%80%93%20the%20desolation%20of%20an%20isolated%2C%20indefinite%20old%20age.%20Home%20nurses%20are%20often%20the%20last%20true%20relationships%20of%20many%20of%20these%20seniors%2C%20for%20the%20children%20have%20been%20reduced%20to%20large%20photos%20on%20walls%20of%20inner%20rooms%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20the%20end%20of%20the%20journey%20from%20illness%20to%20hospital%2C%20then%20from%20hospital%20to%20the%20restrictions%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20bed.%E2%80%9D%20It%20is%20hard%20sometimes%20to%20love%20that%20nurse%20even%20if%20one%20is%20grateful%20to%20her%3A%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20smile%20of%20friendship%20lay%20dead%20on%20her%20lips%E2%80%A6when%20she%20held%20the%20thin%2C%20twig-like%20arms%2C%20Sujatha%20%5Bthe%20nurse%5D%20felt%20that%20the%20muscles%2C%20loose%20and%20hanging%2C%20were%20as%20soft%20as%20clouds%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22'Zeherkhurani'%3A%20Nirmala%20Bhuradia's%20Latest%20Novel%20Holds%20a%20Mirror%20to%20Our%20Times%20Consumed%20by%20Hate%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fzeherkhurani-nirmala-bhuradias-latest-novel-holds-mirror-to-our-times-consumed-by-hate%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Zeherkhurani%E2%80%99%3A%20Nirmala%20Bhuradia%E2%80%99s%20Latest%20Novel%20Holds%20a%20Mirror%20to%20Our%20Times%20Consumed%20by%20Hate%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20dispossessions%20too%20%E2%80%93%20Indugopan%E2%80%99s%20story%20writes%20of%20those%20who%20work%20in%20airports%20performing%20menial%20labour.%20Airports%20are%20places%20of%20middle-class%20stress%2C%20a%20stress%20often%20loaded%20onto%20workers%20%E2%80%93%20thus%2C%20when%20the%20protagonist%20Muniyandi%20is%20interrogated%20by%20a%20policeman%2C%20he%20replies%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20scared%20of%20dying%20in%20custody%2C%20Saare%20%5BSir%5D.%20The%20daily%20wages%20I%20get%2C%20my%20family%20can%20make%20if%20they%20take%20to%20begging.%E2%80%9D%20These%20men%20take%20pains%20to%20educate%20themselves%2C%20but%20this%20is%20two-edged%3A%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20your%20literacy%20will%20show%20when%20you%20speak%E2%80%94and%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20headache.%20The%20listener%20won%E2%80%99t%20like%20it.%E2%80%9D%20Such%20a%20dispossession%20is%20only%20topped%20by%20the%20even%20more%20brutal%20maiming%20of%20harmless%20animals%20%E2%80%93%20for%20example%2C%20the%20turtles%20that%20routinely%20lose%20their%20feet%20due%20to%20the%20propellers%20of%20commercial%20fishing%20that%20trouble%20Kerala%E2%80%99s%20coastline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20stores%20are%20examples%20of%20fine%20storytelling.%20Unni%20writes%20humorously%20of%20how%20a%20family%20in%20financial%20distress%20realises%20that%20they%20can%20refurbish%20their%20small%20house%20temple%20into%20one%20that%20claims%20to%20particularly%20cure%20sexual%20ailments%20%E2%80%93%20a%20foul-mouthed%20neighbour%20is%20promoted%20to%20oracle%2C%20a%20Bastar%20statuette%20to%20main%20deity%2C%20and%20the%20priest%20is%20given%20motivational%20books%20to%20read%20in%20case%20he%20is%20bored.%20Even%20more%20moving%20and%20elaborated%20storytelling%20(with%20themes%20of%20police%20firing%2C%20and%20the%20caste%20systems%20within%20Kerala%20Christianity)%20are%20provided%20in%20the%20exceptional%20stories%20of%20Shajikumar%20and%20Prince%20Aymanam.%20It%20would%20be%20hard%20to%20adequately%20invoke%20here%20their%20dexterity%20with%20the%20invocations%20of%20brute%20fact%2C%20heroic%20histories%2C%20corrupt%20political%20and%20media%20manipulations%20of%20caste-tragedy%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20continual%20oscillations%20of%20personal%20and%20community%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDevika%20retains%20the%20flavour%20of%20Malayalam%20through%20many%20means%20%E2%80%93%20sometimes%20through%20spelling%20(%E2%80%98intellectchuals%E2%80%9D)%2C%20by%20pronunciation%20and%20idiomatic%20usage%20(%E2%80%9C%20Now%20its%20all%20terrorists%20and%20cheats%E2%80%94comblete!%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20%E2%80%9C%20drivers%20are%20beg%E2%80%99nning%20to%20spout%20lit%E2%80%99rature%3F%E2%80%9D)%2C%20and%20often%20by%20leaving%20the%20Malayalam%20in%20roman%20script%20before%20providing%20an%20approximate%20translation.%20The%20adept%20translations%20capture%20well%20the%20colloquial%20and%20idiomatic%20speech.%20All%20this%20helps%20restore%20verve%20and%20sparkle%20to%20a%20language%20that%20is%20always%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20being%20dulled%20by%20translation.%20By%20keeping%20the%20pungency%20and%20heat%20of%20language%20so%20alive%2C%20Devika%20gives%20us%20as%20complete%20and%20satisfying%20a%20synoptic%20picture%20of%20the%20literary%20scene%20of%20a%20major%20culture%20as%20is%20reasonably%20possible%20in%20a%20single%20volume%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENikhil%20Govind%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Literature%20at%20the%20Manipal%20Centre%20of%20Humanities%2C%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708852549000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25144446%2Fgaurav-kumar-33Z4FsBTiAY-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fstories-that-unveil-the-many-worlds-in-kerala%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Feeling%20Kerala%3A%20An%20Anthology%20of%20Contemporary%20Malayalam%20Stories'%2C%20translated%20by%20J.%20Devika%2C%20gives%20us%20as%20complete%20and%20satisfying%20a%20synoptic%20picture%20of%20the%20literary%20scene%20of%20a%20major%20culture%20as%20is%20reasonably%20possible%20in%20a%20single%20volume%20collection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fstories-that-unveil-the-many-worlds-in-kerala%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Farmers%20at%20Shambhu%20Border%20Say%2C%20'We%20Now%20Feel%20Like%20Outsiders%20in%20Our%20Own%20Country'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131354%2Ffarmer-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20have%20the%20powers%20that%20be%20made%20the%20Punjab-Haryana%20border%20un-crossable%20for%20protesting%20farmers%20trying%20to%20reach%20Delhi%2C%20they%20have%20also%20made%20it%20well-nigh%20impossible%20for%20ordinary%20citizens%20to%20visit%20the%20Shambhu%20toll%20plaza%20and%20express%20solidarity%20with%20their%20%3Cem%3Eannadatas%3C%2Fem%3E%20camped%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20approaching%20Shambhu%20border%20from%20Haryana%20will%20find%20approach%20roads%20blocked%20and%20guarded%20by%20the%20police.%20They%20will%20also%20likely%20find%20Google%20Maps%20not%20working%20as%20internet%20access%20has%20been%20restricted%20across%20huge%20swathes%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20nearly%2050-km%20detour%20through%20rural%20Punjab%2C%20my%20taxi%20driver%20managed%20to%20get%20us%20to%20the%20tail%20end%20of%20the%20caravan%20of%20tractors%2C%20trolleys%20and%20tents%20stretching%20for%2010%20km%20from%20the%20Shambhu%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20farmers%20sitting%20on%20a%20mattress%20beneath%20the%20shade%20of%20their%20tractor%20brought%20back%20to%20memory%20the%20very%20first%20group%20of%20protesting%20farmers%20I%20ever%20met%2C%20at%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Ghazipur%20border%20on%20a%20cold%2C%20smoggy%20December%20evening%20in%202020.%20They%20too%20had%20been%20sitting%20on%20a%20mattress%20by%20the%20side%20of%20the%20Meerut%20Express%20Highway.%20I%20still%20remember%20the%20very%20first%20question%20those%20Sikh%20farmers%20had%20asked%20me%20as%20I%20had%20approached%20them.%20%E2%80%9CHave%20you%20had%20something%20to%20eat%3F%E2%80%9D%20Certainly%20not%20the%20kind%20of%20question%20%E2%80%98terrorists%E2%80%99%20ask.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20this%20current%20group%20of%20farmers%20to%20explain%20their%20protest%20in%20terms%20simple%20enough%20for%20a%20non-farmer%20to%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131439%2Ffarmer-4.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131439%2Ffarmer-4.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131439%2Ffarmer-4-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131439%2Ffarmer-4-1024x577.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698757%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22676%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFarmers%20at%20Shambhu%20border.%20Photo%3A%20Rohit%20Kumar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmrit%20Singh%2C%20who%20farms%20a%20three-acre%20plot%20of%20land%20outside%20Amritsar%2C%20obliged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20issue%20of%20minimum%20support%20price%20is%20not%20just%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20issue%2C%20it%20is%20something%20that%20concerns%20everyone%20in%20India%2C%20because%20everyone%20needs%20to%20eat!%C2%A0%20MSP%20simply%20means%20a%20fair%20price%20below%20which%20we%20should%20not%20have%20to%20sell%20our%20produce.%20While%20there%20is%20MSP%20for%20wheat%20and%20rice%2C%20there%20is%20no%20MSP%20for%20tomatoes%2C%20onions%20and%20other%20fruit%20and%20vegetables.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20we%20end%20up%20selling%20our%20produce%20for%20two%20or%20three%20rupees%20a%20kilo%2C%20but%20you%20end%20up%20buying%20it%20for%2080%2C%20100%2C%20or%20even%20150%20rupees%20a%20kilo!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20went%20on%20to%20explain%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20manufacturer%20who%20made%20the%20shirt%20I%20am%20wearing%20fixed%20a%20price%20he%20wanted%20to%20sell%20it%20at.%20But%20we%20farmers%20get%20to%20have%20no%20say%20in%20how%20much%20we%20will%20sell%20our%20crops%20for!%20We%20are%20simply%20asking%20for%20what%20the%20government%20has%20already%20been%20promised%20to%20us%2C%20and%20we%20are%20being%20called%20%3Cem%3Ekhalistanis%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20the%20media!%20Please%20take%20your%20camera%2C%20walk%20around%2C%20and%20see%20for%20yourself%20if%20there%20are%20any%20terrorists%20present!%20Do%20we%20look%20like%20terrorists%20to%20you%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmit%20Singh%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20there%20is%20a%20problem%20at%20home%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%20take%20our%20problems%20to%20the%20head%20of%20the%20house%3F%20Similarly%2C%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20we%20be%20able%20to%20go%20to%20the%20highest%20authorities%20in%20the%20land%20if%20we%20have%20a%20problem%3F%20But%20what%20happens%20when%20we%20do%3F%20We%20end%20up%20getting%20beaten%2C%20teargassed%2C%20and%20shot%2C%20and%20then%20we%20end%20up%20being%20called%20the%20enemy!%20More%20and%20more%20we%20are%20being%20made%20to%20feel%20like%20outsiders%20in%20our%20own%20country.%20To%20tell%20you%20the%20truth%2C%20our%20hearts%20are%20crying.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FRrz7hq3Wry8%3Fsi%3DmYwYMUupH-jP_aq9%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20elderly%20farmer%20who%20had%20been%20overhearing%20the%20conversation%20interrupted.%20%E2%80%9CLook%20at%20all%20these%20farmers%20here!%20None%20of%20them%20are%20rich.%20Some%20own%20two%20acres%20of%20land%2C%20some%20three.%20Many%20of%20them%20barely%20manage%20to%20grow%20enough%20to%20feed%20even%20their%20own%20families!%20And%20yet%2C%20these%20are%20the%20people%20who%20are%20being%20bombed%20and%20shot!%20Modi%20should%20be%20ashamed%20of%20himself!%20Instead%20of%20interviewing%20us%2C%20why%20don%E2%80%99t%20you%20interview%20Modi%20and%20ask%20him%20what%20he%20is%20doing%3F!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20anger%20in%20his%20voice%20rising%2C%20the%20elderly%20man%20pointed%20to%20the%20other%20elderly%20farmers%20sitting%20there.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20knees%20are%20damaged%2C%20this%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20legs%20hurt%2C%20this%20other%20farmer%20here%20can%20barely%20walk!%20None%20of%20us%20are%20sitting%20here%20because%20we%20are%20happy%20to%2C%20you%20know%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20crossed%20hundreds%20of%20tractors%20and%20trolleys%20as%20I%20walked%20towards%20the%20bridge%20across%20Ghaggar%20river%20which%20has%20now%20become%20the%20de%20facto%20border%20between%20the%20paramilitary%20and%20the%20farmers.%20Every%2050%20feet%20or%20so%2C%20someone%20had%20set%20up%20a%20%3Cem%3Elangar%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20was%20serving%20tea%2C%20food%20or%20water.%20An%20elderly%20gentleman%20in%20the%20back%20of%20a%20tempo%20offered%20water%20bottles%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekinoos%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20everyone%20who%20passed%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131507%2Ffarmer-2.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131507%2Ffarmer-2.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131507%2Ffarmer-2-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131507%2Ffarmer-2-1024x577.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698758%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22676%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFarmers%20at%20Shambhu%20border.%20Photo%3A%20Rohit%20Kumar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20100%20meters%20from%20the%20paramilitary%20barricade%2C%20a%20group%20of%20farmers%20stood%20guard%20next%20to%20a%20thick%20rope%20that%20had%20cordoned%20off%20a%20hundred-meter%20stretch%20of%20empty%20road%20now%20considered%20%E2%80%9Cno%20man%E2%80%99s%20land%E2%80%9D.%20The%20farmers%20have%20been%20instructed%20not%20to%20go%20beyond%20that%20rope.%20Strewn%20all%20over%20the%20road%20were%20gunny%20sacks%20which%20the%20farmers%20had%20thrown%20on%20exploding%20tear%20gas%20canisters%20to%20try%20and%20contain%20the%20smoke.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBarely%20300%20metres%20from%20the%20border%2C%20a%20group%20called%20the%20United%20Sikhs%20had%20set%20up%20a%20medical%20camp%20for%20those%20injured%20in%20the%20recent%20tear%20gas%20shelling.%20They%20showed%20me%20huge%20rubber%20bullets%20and%20exploded%20tear%20gas%20cannisters%20and%20told%20me%20that%20military%20grade%20weapons%20were%20used%20on%20the%20farmers.%20They%20also%20told%20me%20that%20a%20tear%20gas%20cannister%20fired%20from%20a%20drone%20exploded%20right%20next%20to%20their%20tent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CElderly%20people%20have%20inhaled%20tear%20gas%2C%20and%20it%20has%20damaged%20their%20lungs.%20We%20have%20removed%20pellets%20from%20the%20bodies%20of%20the%20injured.%20Please%20go%20to%20Rajpura%20hospital%20and%20see%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20injured%20for%20yourself.%20What%20has%20happened%20here%20is%20very%2C%20very%20wrong!%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20short%20distance%20away%2C%20Dr%20Harpreet%20Singh%20and%20Dr%20Ravinder%20Singh%2C%20two%20young%20doctors%20from%20Hoshiarpur%20were%20distributing%20medicines%20from%20the%20boot%20of%20their%20car.%20Mentioning%20their%20proximity%20to%20%E2%80%98ground%20zero%E2%80%99%2C%20I%20asked%20if%20they%20were%20afraid%20of%20getting%20injured%20in%20police%20and%20paramilitary%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Harpreet%20smiled%2C%20shook%20his%20head%2C%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20came%20here%2C%20%3Cem%3Esar%20pe%20kafan%20bandh%20ke%20aye%20thhe.%3C%2Fem%3E%20We%20came%20with%20the%20full%20awareness%20that%20we%20too%20could%20get%20injured%20or%20killed.%20But%20we%20are%20not%20afraid.%20We%20are%20here%20to%20fight%20for%20our%20rights.%20Our%20Guru%20Gobind%20Singh%20Ji%20Maharaj%20has%20taught%20us%20that%20just%20as%20it%20is%20a%20sin%20to%20commit%20wrongdoing%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20sin%20to%20tolerate%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20shook%20their%20hands%20and%20told%20them%20I%20admired%20their%20courage%20and%20selflessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManinder%20Singh%2C%20a%20homemaker%2C%20told%20me%20she%20comes%20every%20morning%20to%20do%20%3Cem%3Eseva%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20serve%20%3Cem%3Elangar%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20the%20protestors%2C%20and%20then%20goes%20back%20home%20in%20the%20evening.%20She%20also%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20tell%20me%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20Guru%20Nanak%20Dev%20ji%20has%20not%20made%20us%20cowards.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELakhvir%20Singh%2C%20a%20farmer%20from%20Sri%20Muktsar%20Sahib%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CGive%20us%20MSP%20for%20all%2023%20crops%20and%20we%20will%20diversify%20our%20crop%20cultivation%20and%20grow%20the%20crops%20that%20will%20neither%20deplete%20the%20water%20table%20nor%20compel%20us%20to%20burn%20%3Cem%3Eparali%3C%2Fem%3E%20(stubble)%20and%20pollute%20the%20air.%20We%20are%20not%20just%20fighting%20for%20ourselves%2C%20we%20are%20fighting%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20farmers%20all%20over%20India.%20Farmers%20in%20Bihar%20are%20selling%20their%20rice%20for%20Rs%201%2C300%20a%20quintal%20whereas%20MSP%20for%20rice%20is%20Rs%202%2C200.%20We%20care%20about%20them%20too.%20Give%20us%20MSP%20based%20on%20Dr%20%5BM.S.%5D%20Swaminathan%E2%80%99s%20C2%2B50%25%20formula%20and%20we%20will%20go%20home.%20We%20aren%E2%80%99t%20mad%20to%20want%20to%20sit%20here%20on%20the%20road%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131532%2Ffarmer-3.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131532%2Ffarmer-3.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131532%2Ffarmer-3-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131532%2Ffarmer-3-1024x577.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698759%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22676%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20farmer%20at%20Shambhu%20border.%20Photo%3A%20Rohit%20Kumar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20farmers%20did%20not%20conceal%20their%20pain%20at%20being%20attacked%20by%20%E2%80%9Ctheir%20own%20sons%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20barricading%E2%80%9D.%20While%20the%20quiet%20tenacity%20and%20courage%20of%20the%20farmers%20continues%20to%20be%20inspiring%2C%20it%20is%20deeply%20alarming%20is%20to%20see%20the%20massive%20deficit%20of%20trust%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20heavy-handedness%20and%20lack%20of%20empathy%20has%20created%20not%20just%20between%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekisan%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3Esarkaar%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebut%20also%20between%20the%3Cem%3E%20kisan%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20the%20%3Cem%3Ejawaan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20elderly%20farmer%20who%20did%20not%20wish%20to%20be%20named%20perhaps%20expressed%20the%20tragedy%20of%20the%20situation%20best%20when%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20forgive%20those%20who%20have%20hurt%20us%2C%20for%20they%20were%20acting%20under%20orders%2C%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20feed%20you%20for%20that%20is%20what%20we%20do%2C%20but%20we%20will%20never%2C%20ever%20forget%20the%20%3Cem%3Evishvaasghaat%3C%2Fem%3E%20(betray